</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_item  
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_item">
A <b>Resource_item</b> is a definition of something that can occur in the role of a resource within the application context, where
a resource is defined to be something that is needed in order to achieve a specified objective.
The role of the resource item is determined by classification.
<example>
A resource item can be classified as "Facility", "Replaceble unit" or "Package".
</example>
</ext_description>
