<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_item.description">
a description of the resource.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_item  Attribute: resource_item 
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item.resource_item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_item.resource_item">
the item type or actual item, that is defined to act in the role of a resource within the application context.
<example>
A resource_item can be a product, product category, product version, serialized product, or person.
</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Resource_item_arm  Entity: Resource_item_assignment  
   <express_ref linkend="resource_item:arm:Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_assignment"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Resource_item_arm.Resource_item_assignment">
A <b>Resource_item_assignment</b> is an association of a resource item with products, product types, etc, 
to which the resource_item applies.
The role of the assignment is determined by classification.
<example>
The assignment can be classified as "Applicable_to" or "Aquired_for".
</example>
</ext_description>
